{
  "doc_id": "10420",
  "text": "Earlier, Kim et al. [CITATION_1] documented that ADC is a useful tool to differentiate between malignant and benign tissue in both peripheral and transitional zone based on 3 Tesla phased array coil study at 0 and 1000 s/mm 2 values. No correlation was established between ADC value and Gleason score of malignant tissue. Similar investigations were performed by Gibbs et al. [CITATION_2] and Pickles et al. [CITATION_3] at values = 0 and 500 s/mm 2 , only differentiating tumor from normal peripheral zone.",
